---
description: Restaurant Admin Builder project rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Project: Restaurant Website Admin Builder

Stack:
- Next.js App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Supabase Auth
- Supabase Postgres
- Supabase Storage
- Vercel

Architecture:
- Use one Supabase project.
- Use one Next.js app.
- Use one Vercel deployment.
- Separate restaurant data by restaurant_id.
- Do not create separate apps per restaurant.
- Do not create separate Vercel deployments per restaurant in MVP.
- Do not build a drag-and-drop editor.
- Do not build online ordering or payments in MVP.
- Public restaurant pages live at /r/[slug].
- Admin pages live under /dashboard.

Target users:
- Older small restaurant owners in Minnesota.
- UI must be simple, large, clear, and easy to use.
- Prefer template-based design controls over free-form editing.
- Use plain language in the UI.

Security:
- Never expose Supabase service_role key on the client.
- All restaurant-owned data must be protected with RLS.
- Restaurant owners can only access restaurants where they are members.
- Public users can only read published restaurant data.
